to really change what it
is that people believed
about the candidates.

20:33.500 --> 20:37.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The director of national
intelligence has said
that this occurred.

20:37.033 --> 20:40.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not a -- fake news is
a term that's now become
politicized in its own way.

20:40.733 --> 20:44.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But from the intelligence
community's perspective,
this is a known fact.

20:44.067 --> 20:47.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then the third piece --
is this the one that I think
we're at the stage now of trying

20:47.067 --> 20:51.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to learn more about --
is whether or not and
to what degree there
were contacts between

20:51.467 --> 20:56.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian representatives
and elements perhaps of
Trump's campaign, his
advisers or his associates.

20:58.433 --> 21:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's really where
the center of gravity is
moving in the investigation.

21:00.433 --> 21:02.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: John
Sipher, you spent a
quarter-century in the CIA.

21:02.467 --> 21:06.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Do all of those allegations
against the Russians and their
involvement, does this all ring

21:06.367 --> 21:07.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
true to you?

21:07.633 --> 21:09.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER, Former CIA
Officer: Oh, absolutely.

21:09.267 --> 21:11.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Russians have been doing
this for decades, if
not hundreds of years.

21:11.767 --> 21:14.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is what they do.

21:14.233 --> 21:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's interesting about this
is what fertile soil it took
place on, the fact that these

21:18.633 --> 21:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
type of things, some of it
quite sloppy and open, actually
caused the problems they did

21:24.233 --> 21:25.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for us.

21:25.900 --> 21:26.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Do you
mean fertile soil here
in the United States?

21:26.700 --> 21:27.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER: I do.

21:27.467 --> 21:29.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I do.

21:29.500 --> 21:33.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fact that they were able to
break in and steal DNC e-mails
and take advantage of that,

21:34.600 --> 21:36.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I'm surprised at
the effect that had.

21:36.667 --> 21:40.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it's unusual that you
had a campaign that was able
to use that and spin that up

21:40.333 --> 21:43.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and deal with the
Russian service here.

21:43.267 --> 21:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What I find interesting is
that there is a lot of concern
that the Trump campaign was

21:47.500 --> 21:51.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying they didn't have
improper contact with
Russians during the campaign.

21:51.067 --> 21:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And my question would be,
what is proper contact?

21:55.300 --> 21:58.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Did they have contacts with
Germans, Indians, Japanese?

21:58.833 --> 22:00.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Why with Russians?

22:00.967 --> 22:03.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Why would a campaign in the
United States need to have
any contact with Russians?

22:03.933 --> 22:07.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: There could
be innocent explanations,
if members to have the Trump

22:07.933 --> 22:10.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
campaign or his entourage
were talking with Russians.

22:10.533 --> 22:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Couldn't there be innocent
explanations for those?

22:12.600 --> 22:16.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EVAN OSNOS: Well, I think
that's the reason why we need
now a robust, independent and

22:16.400 --> 22:18.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thorough investigation.

22:18.433 --> 22:21.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We decided as an institution
that we needed to understand
this as best we could.

22:21.467 --> 22:22.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We interviewed dozens of people.

22:22.800 --> 22:24.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We spent months on this.

22:24.333 --> 22:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I consider it the very
beginning of chapter one.

22:27.300 --> 22:31.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are now in a position where
the legislative branch, the
executive branch has the ability

22:31.167 --> 22:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to go out and say, well,
what was the full universe of
contacts, what were the nature

22:34.433 --> 22:37.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of those contacts, and were they
serving the American public,
and do we know everything

22:37.900 --> 22:39.167 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
we can?

22:39.167 --> 22:41.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Because, look, we
did that for 9/11.

22:41.667 --> 22:45.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We established a bipartisan,
independent commission
composed of five Republicans
and five Democrats.

22:45.167 --> 22:48.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, as a result, we know a
huge amount about what happened.

22:48.267 --> 22:50.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We don't know that
yet about this event.

22:50.367 --> 22:52.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think we are really at
the stage where we're trying
to decide, what are the right

22:52.233 --> 22:54.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
investigative tools and
who is going to do it?

22:54.300 --> 22:57.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: John, let's
just say that the evidence bears
out that the Russians really

22:57.467 --> 23:00.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
were trying to put their
thumb on the scale here.

23:00.300 --> 23:04.167 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What were their
ambitions, in your sense?

23:04.167 --> 23:05.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What would they be
trying to do here?

23:05.367 --> 23:07.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER: This is
not much of a surprise.

23:07.367 --> 23:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Vladimir Putin's interests
have always been to divide
the United States from Europe.

23:11.200 --> 23:14.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has a zero sum view of
working with the United States.

23:14.333 --> 23:18.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So anything that causes
chaos or creates problems
here is a win for him.

23:18.800 --> 23:22.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We see the same thing
happening now in France,
Germany, the Balkans.

23:22.800 --> 23:25.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's even working with the
Taliban in Afghanistan.

23:25.100 --> 23:27.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, this is the kind
of thing they do.

23:27.733 --> 23:32.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their goal is to
essentially create
fissures in our alliances.

23:34.733 --> 23:38.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Anything that creates chaos and
tries to provide some sort of
moral equivalence between his

23:38.233 --> 23:42.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regime and the West, he likes
to say that, oh, this is no
different than you guys messing

23:42.933 --> 23:45.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
around#~ in Libya and Egypt and
Syria and those type of things.

23:45.267 --> 23:48.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EVAN OSNOS: One of the
things, the surprise for
me in the course of this
work was to discover,

23:48.733 --> 23:52.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in effect, that the United
States was susceptible to
this kind of operation.

23:52.233 --> 23:55.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I spoke to people who used
to work on this in the State
Department who said, a couple

23:55.533 --> 23:59.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of years ago, we were worried
that Moldova, for instance,
would be vulnerable to this

23:59.500 --> 24:00.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
kind of interference.

24:00.767 --> 24:01.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
Little, teeny Moldova.

24:01.567 --> 24:02.567 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

24:02.567 --> 24:04.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
EVAN OSNOS: Exactly.

24:04.633 --> 24:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, in a sense, the agents
behind this operation -- and
that's really what this was

24:07.433 --> 24:11.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - it was an intelligence
operation -- discovered that our
politics were so divided, people

24:11.333 --> 24:16.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were already open to a
highly kind of propagandistic
form of political
communication, that we were

24:18.967 --> 24:22.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a prime target, in effect,
a soft target for this kind
of influence operation.

24:22.433 --> 24:25.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: One of the
things I was struck by in your
article is that you wrote,

24:25.567 --> 24:30.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
towards the end of your piece,
where you described how some of
the intelligence agents think

24:32.600 --> 24:36.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that this was more of
an improvisation on
behalf of the Russians,
not a sort of strategic

24:36.867 --> 24:38.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
campaign.

24:38.100 --> 24:40.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Can you explain the
distinction there?

24:40.133 --> 24:42.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EVAN OSNOS: Well,
speaking broadly about
sort of the impression
that people have who are

24:42.067 --> 24:45.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
focused on this issue, is that
there's one way to think of it.

24:45.867 --> 24:50.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you look at this dossier
of unverified claims that was
submitted earlier to the FBI

24:52.867 --> 24:56.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and was then presented to the
president, one of the claims
in there was that this was a

24:56.400 --> 25:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
longstanding, five-, six-,
seven-year operation to
cultivate Donald Trump.

25:00.200 --> 25:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, at the moment, what
you find is that more people
who are focused on this issue

25:03.433 --> 25:07.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are inclined to believe that
this was an improvisation
that was changing.

25:07.033 --> 25:11.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There were elements that were
brought in at different points,
meaning it may have started

25:11.000 --> 25:13.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as a hacking operation.

25:13.167 --> 25:17.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It may have started as
an intelligence -- it
may have started as an
influence operation.

25:19.067 --> 25:21.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the idea that this started
six, seven years ago, with a
discrete, fully formed plan

25:21.933 --> 25:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with a clear objective is
hard to defend at this point.

25:25.200 --> 25:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that's one of the
reasons why we need to learn
more, because we don't know

25:28.000 --> 25:30.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
exactly when and how it started.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Why would the
Russians have been interested
in Donald Trump back then?

25:32.167 --> 25:34.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Because, then, he was
a reality TV star.

25:34.900 --> 25:36.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He had no intention, seemingly,
of running for office.

25:36.933 --> 25:38.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER: I don't
know that they did.

25:38.867 --> 25:41.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't think we have that
information, if they were
particularly interested in him.

25:41.667 --> 25:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They certainly do collect
on any American of
interest who visits Russia.

25:44.733 --> 25:49.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The notion that they would
have videotapes in hotel rooms
or follow people around or

25:49.567 --> 25:53.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
try to collect compromising
information on people,
this is what they do.

25:53.533 --> 25:57.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: John, how
does what we're seeing today
compare to what the Soviets used

25:57.700 --> 25:59.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to do back in the USSR?

25:59.800 --> 26:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN SIPHER: What they're
doing now is very similar
to what they did before.

26:01.900 --> 26:04.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They just have new tools.

26:04.100 --> 26:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have Mr. Snowden, who
gives them a lot of information
about the kind of things we

26:07.733 --> 26:09.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have and where to attack.

26:09.833 --> 26:14.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And they have some
really talented computer
programmers and hackers
there in Russia that...

26:16.000 --> 26:16.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And the
Internet more broadly.

26:16.800 --> 26:17.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER: Right.

26:17.733 --> 26:18.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Exactly.

26:18.733 --> 26:20.767 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Exactly.

26:20.767 --> 26:22.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Evan Osnos, John Sipher,
thank you both very much.

26:22.000 --> 26:25.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN SIPHER: Thank you.

26:25.900 --> 26:30.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
EVAN OSNOS: Glad to be here.

26:32.933 --> 26:36.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now what
hospitals fear about
the possible costs of
repealing and replacing

26:38.433 --> 26:40.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the health care law.

26:40.500 --> 26:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Efforts by President Trump and
congressional Republicans to
unravel the Affordable Care

26:44.733 --> 26:48.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Act are unnerving many
hospital executives.

26:48.133 --> 26:52.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say they're worried about
big changes to their bottom
line, particularly after they

26:52.600 --> 26:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
overhauled how care is delivered
in response to the health
law's rewards and penalties.

26:59.500 --> 27:02.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
While Republicans try to figure
out their game plan, special
correspondent Sarah Varney

27:02.800 --> 27:06.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
