27:13.400 --> 27:16.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Driving to work
amid the barren winter fields
in Northern Illinois, Cathie

27:17.833 --> 27:19.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Chapman is worried
about the future.

27:19.267 --> 27:21.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She lost her job after a
nearby rural hospital closed.

27:21.967 --> 27:24.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CATHIE CHAPMAN, Perry Memorial
Hospital: I was really lucky.

27:24.033 --> 27:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I found another great hospital
to work in with a wonderful
group of people who deliver

27:28.000 --> 27:29.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
high-quality care.

27:29.433 --> 27:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But not everyone was as lucky.

27:31.633 --> 27:36.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: And as Republicans
work to dismantle the Affordable
Care Act, she wonders if it

27:36.033 --> 27:38.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
might happen again.

27:38.167 --> 27:42.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now she runs the pharmacy
at Perry Memorial in
Princeton, Illinois.

27:42.400 --> 27:45.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And she's watching
the Republicans'
repeal efforts warily.

27:45.300 --> 27:50.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CATHIE CHAPMAN: I think
everybody who works in health
care now feels a little uneasy.

27:50.100 --> 27:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even if you're a large,
profitable hospital,
we don't know what's
coming around the corner,

27:54.100 --> 27:56.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and how it will affect us.

27:56.500 --> 28:00.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Rural
hospitals have long
struggled to stay open:
They have far fewer patients

28:00.267 --> 28:02.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and thin margins.

28:02.300 --> 28:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dozens have closed across the
country in recent years, mostly
in states that didn't expand

28:06.133 --> 28:08.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Medicaid.

28:08.467 --> 28:13.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, in Illinois, which did
extend Medicaid to nearly all
poor adults, patients at Perry

28:15.833 --> 28:20.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Memorial have gained
coverage under the
Affordable Care Act and many
hospitals have found firmer

28:21.233 --> 28:23.267 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
footing.

28:23.267 --> 28:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Annette Schnabel, the
hospital's CEO, says if large
numbers of people lose their

28:30.900 --> 28:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
insurance under the Republicans'
replacement, the hospital's
finances and its patients would

28:37.833 --> 28:41.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be at risk, especially after
the hospital has invested so
much money and time in complying

28:42.233 --> 28:44.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with the health law.

28:44.267 --> 28:46.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANNETTE SCHNABEL, CEO, Perry
Memorial Hospital: We have spent
the last six years gearing up

28:46.300 --> 28:51.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
towards everything that we were
responsible for doing in the
ACA, and the idea of we might

28:53.200 --> 28:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have to totally go a different
direction or how will we do
that, it's going to take a

28:55.633 --> 28:56.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lot of work.

28:56.900 --> 28:59.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's a lot of effort
that is going into this.

28:59.400 --> 29:03.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: And for
some hospitals to survive
or break even, it will
require Congress to

29:05.500 --> 29:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
restore billions of dollars
in funding that kept hospitals
afloat before the law took

29:09.767 --> 29:11.867 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
effect.

29:11.867 --> 29:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hospitals made a high-stakes
trade when they signed on
to the Affordable Care Act.

29:14.400 --> 29:18.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They agreed to massive
cuts in federal aid that
defrayed the cost of
caring for the uninsured.

29:18.733 --> 29:23.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In exchange, they would
