44:06.900 --> 44:11.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Next: a preview of a new
PBS documentary series,
"Africa's Great Civilizations."

44:21.067 --> 44:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Audie Cornish of NPR's "All
Things Considered" has our look.

44:25.200 --> 44:29.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: The history of
the African continent, home to
the 15 percent of the world's

44:29.733 --> 44:32.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
population, remains
a mystery for many.

44:32.667 --> 44:37.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Historian and Harvard Professor
Henry Louis Gates Jr. admits,
in his youth, it was a place

44:37.067 --> 44:39.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he rarely considered.

44:39.533 --> 44:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now he has a new PBS
documentary series that
reveals great moments in
the continent's pre-colonial

44:44.433 --> 44:45.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
history.

44:45.700 --> 44:47.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's called "Africa's
Great Civilizations."

44:47.633 --> 44:49.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He joins me now to
discuss that work.

44:49.767 --> 44:51.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Henry Louis Gates Jr.,
welcome to the program.

44:51.200 --> 44:52.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.,
Harvard University: Thanks.

44:52.133 --> 44:54.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thanks for having me on.

44:54.300 --> 44:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
AUDIE CORNISH: So, you
have tackled all kinds
of African-American
history, but this goes

44:57.433 --> 45:00.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
all the way back, way
back to cave paintings.

45:00.200 --> 45:02.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, what was the
genesis of this idea?

45:02.200 --> 45:06.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: I wanted
to do a comprehensive history
of Africa, and this is it.

45:08.100 --> 45:08.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I have been thinking
about it five years.

45:08.967 --> 45:10.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Took us a year to shoot.

45:10.633 --> 45:13.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We went to 12 African countries.

45:13.267 --> 45:18.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's exhilarating,
six-hour series on 200,000
years of African history.

45:20.133 --> 45:22.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I was growing up, Africa
was a place to be avoided,
even for black people.

45:22.867 --> 45:27.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our images of Africa came
from Tarzan and Ramar
and Sheena of the jungle.

45:28.900 --> 45:30.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And we were embarrassed
about Africa.

45:30.933 --> 45:32.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: As you
talked about the effort to
kind of distance, right?

45:32.267 --> 45:34.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was used as an insult
within the community.

45:34.467 --> 45:38.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: You
black African, oh, my God,
that was like the N-word.

45:38.167 --> 45:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But all that changed for me.

45:40.600 --> 45:44.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It began to change in 1960,
when I was 10 years old,
and 17 African nations
became independent.

45:46.733 --> 45:51.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I had a very smart
geography teacher, Mr.
McHenry, our only male teacher.

45:51.600 --> 45:54.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And he was very much
into current events.

45:54.533 --> 45:56.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I was very much into
being a good student.

45:56.533 --> 46:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a lot of the current
events featured these emerging,
new African countries.

46:03.933 --> 46:07.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I mesmerized
romantic sounding, rhythmic
names like Masha Chubay
(ph) and Patrice Lumumba

46:08.800 --> 46:11.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and Mogadishu, words like that.

46:11.033 --> 46:16.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I became fascinated with
Africa, slowly, but surely
making my way to Africa when I

46:16.767 --> 46:18.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
was 19 years old.

46:18.267 --> 46:20.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: I think we can
hear that in your introduction.

46:20.033 --> 46:21.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I want to play a clip of that.

46:21.467 --> 46:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: OK.

46:23.433 --> 46:26.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Africa is the home
of the world's most
ancient civilizations.

46:26.567 --> 46:31.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Far to too often, Africa has
been thought of isolated and
static, but nothing could

46:34.533 --> 46:37.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
be further from the truth.

46:37.067 --> 46:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The roots of every
family tree trace here to
Africa, and so does the
history of civilization.

46:46.133 --> 46:51.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In this series, we will be
going on a journey through
200,000 years of history.

46:53.100 --> 46:57.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will explore great cities
built along Africa's extensive
trade networks, discover art of

46:59.533 --> 47:04.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
unparalleled beauty,
technical brilliance,
and marvel at thousands
of years of breathtaking

47:06.567 --> 47:08.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
architecture.

47:08.700 --> 47:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: What struck me
watching this is that you use
words like merchants and trade

47:12.533 --> 47:14.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and engineering.

47:14.233 --> 47:16.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It seemed like you were
really trying to stress
the achievements here.

47:16.400 --> 47:18.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: Mm-hmm.

47:18.400 --> 47:20.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: Why do you
think those achievements
have been obscured?

47:20.400 --> 47:22.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: I think
the achievements have been
obscured, first of all, because

47:22.467 --> 47:27.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of slavery -- 12.5 million
Africans were shipped across the
Atlantic Ocean between the 16th

47:31.567 --> 47:36.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
century and the 19th century,
12.5 million Africans shipped
to enslavement in the new

47:38.033 --> 47:40.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
world.

47:40.000 --> 47:44.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then after 1884 was the
conference in Berlin, when
European powers sat down, looked

47:45.967 --> 47:49.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at an empty map of Africa,
and basically carved it up
like you carve up a pizza pie.

47:49.100 --> 47:50.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they go, you're Spain.

47:50.200 --> 47:51.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you want?

47:51.200 --> 47:52.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You're Italy.

47:52.200 --> 47:53.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you want?

47:53.200 --> 47:54.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You're England.

47:54.200 --> 47:55.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you want?

47:55.200 --> 47:56.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You're King Leopold.

47:56.200 --> 47:58.167 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He personally got the Congo.

47:58.167 --> 48:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, they had to create a
fiction of Africa as an empty
place or a static place full of

48:00.433 --> 48:02.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
primitive people who
were stuck in time.

48:02.600 --> 48:06.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And those were
ostensibly our ancestors.

48:06.867 --> 48:10.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the pre-colonial world
knew all about Africa.

48:10.133 --> 48:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There wasn't a moment
really since the ancient
Egyptians when Northern
Africa, the Mediterranean

48:17.100 --> 48:21.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
world and the larger world
wasn't in touch with African
civilizations, with some part

48:22.433 --> 48:23.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Africa.

48:23.467 --> 48:25.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The Red Sea was a highway.

48:25.000 --> 48:27.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The Nile was a highway.

48:27.433 --> 48:31.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Sahara was a highway,
particularly after
the domestication of
camels, and the Indian

48:32.167 --> 48:34.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Ocean, highways.

48:34.067 --> 48:38.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The emperor of great Zimbabwe
ate off porcelain plates
that came from China.

48:38.533 --> 48:40.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's the 13th century.

48:40.900 --> 48:42.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's incredible.

48:42.900 --> 48:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Most of Europe's gold
between 1000 A.D. and 1500
A.D. came from West Africa.

48:48.233 --> 48:50.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
All our history
was stolen from us.

48:50.833 --> 48:55.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were robbed of a history
because Europeans wanted to
justify an economic order which

48:57.267 --> 48:59.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
depended upon our
ancestors' exploitation.

48:59.533 --> 49:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AUDIE CORNISH: It's almost as
though you are taking these
stories out of the footnotes

49:03.333 --> 49:05.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of history and elevating them.

49:05.000 --> 49:07.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.:
That's an excellent metaphor.

49:07.233 --> 49:12.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need for the facts of Africa
and African-American history to
be a normal, naturalized part of

49:13.700 --> 49:17.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the curriculum, to be moved from
the footnotes up into the text.

49:17.500 --> 49:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Black History Month is
